What
====
This package contains a module to parse a torrent file and it provides methods to access certain attributes such as 
* tracker url, 
* creation date,
* name of the client that created the torrent, and
* for each file in the torrent
** name, length and checksum of the file

Why
===
I am doing this just as an exercise in Python

How
===
Resources that I used to understand Torrent file structure:
* http://fileformats.wikia.com/wiki/Torrent_file
* http://wiki.theory.org/BitTorrentSpecification
* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bencode
* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torrent_file